-- Ortiz Gets Financing for Two Spanish Wind Parks, Expansion Says
-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e
-- 2012-01-26T07:04:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/ortiz-finances-98-million-spanish-wind-parks-expansion-says.html
Grupo Ortiz, a Spanish construction
company, obtained financing for two new wind parks in the
Almeria region with a combined production capacity of 50
megawatts, Expansion reported. The builder, together with Grupo
Ibereolica and an investment fund, set up a company to develop
the projects for 75 million euros ($98 million), getting part of
the funding from Spanish banks  Banco Santander SA (SAN) ,  Banco Popular
Espanol SA (POP)  and Banco Sabadell SA, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Todd White at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  